# Frontend Quality (Astro)

## Platform
- Build as a static Astro site suitable for GitHub Pages.
- Prefer zero-JS pages unless interactivity is required.

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML landmarks and heading hierarchy.
- Provide alt text for all meaningful images.
- Ensure colour contrast and keyboard accessibility.

## Performance
- Optimise and size images appropriately.
- Avoid heavy client-side bundles unless justified.
- Keep layout stable; avoid avoidable cumulative layout shift.

## Consistency
- Reuse shared layout/components for navigation, page headers, and callouts.
- Keep typography, spacing, and code block style consistent across pages.